Maven + Git + Jenkins Steps (Assignment)

1. Create Maven Project in Git

1.1 Create Git Repository
- Go to GitHub → New Repository
- Repository name: simple-calculator-maven
- Description: Simple calculator using Maven
- Visibility: Public/Private
- Do NOT initialize with README/.gitignore
- Click Create Repository

1.2 Create Project Structure
simple-calculator-maven
 ├── pom.xml
 ├── src
 │   ├── main/java/com/example/App.java
 │   └── test/java/com/example/AppTest.java

1.3 Add pom.xml
Add file → pom.xml

<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0">
    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>
    <groupId>com.example</groupId>
    <artifactId>simple-calculator-maven</artifactId>
    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
    <dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>junit</groupId>
            <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
            <version>4.13.2</version>
            <scope>test</scope>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>
</project>

1.4 Add App.java
Path: src/main/java/com/example/App.java

package com.example;

public class App {
    public int add(int a, int b) { return a + b; }
    public int sub(int a, int b) { return a - b; }
    public int mul(int a, int b) { return a * b; }
    public int div(int a, int b) { return a / b; }
}

1.5 Add AppTest.java
Path: src/test/java/com/example/AppTest.java

package com.example;

import org.junit.Test;
import static org.junit.Assert.*;

public class AppTest {
    App app = new App();

    @Test
    public void testAdd() { assertEquals(5, app.add(2, 3)); }

    @Test
    public void testSub() { assertEquals(1, app.sub(3, 2)); }

    @Test
    public void testMul() { assertEquals(6, app.mul(2, 3)); }

    @Test
    public void testDiv() { assertEquals(2, app.div(4, 2)); }
}

2. Push and Clone Repository
- VS Code → Ctrl+Shift+P → Git Clone
- Paste repo URL
- Open folder and verify structure

3. Build Maven Project
mvn compile
mvn test
mvn clean install

4. Create Jenkins Pipeline

- New Item → Pipeline
- Name: simple-calculator-pipeline

Pipeline Script:

pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage('Clone') {
            steps {
                git 'YOUR_GITHUB_REPO_URL'
            }
        }
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                bat 'mvn compile'
            }
        }
        stage('Test') {
            steps {
                bat 'mvn test'
            }
        }
        stage('Package') {
            steps {
                bat 'mvn clean install'
            }
        }
    }
}

- Click Build Now
- Verify success

